Alpacas: 
farmed for fibers. 
increasing interest in the fibers. 
lots of history


History:
6000 years and began in south america (Incas of Peru especially)
Used for textiles, food, and labor
almost destroyed because of the spanish invasion - 90% killed
survived in the mountains
rediscovered before industrial revolution and helped a select few gain a lot of wealth


Farming:
coats: huacaya and suri
lots of colors
growing interest in fashion so more are being raised in europe to meet demand
bunches in australia
